# Windows Path and Docker Rules

## Docker Container Networking
When working with Docker on Windows, container networking follows these rules:

1. Container-to-Container:
   ```yaml
   # CORRECT - Use service name and internal port
   postgresql://postgres:postgres@timescaledb:5432/postgres
   ```

2. Host-to-Container:
   ```yaml
   # CORRECT - Use localhost and mapped port
   postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5433/postgres
   ```

## Windows Path Formats
When working with paths on Windows:

1. In Docker volumes and mounts:
   ```yaml
   # CORRECT
   - ./data:/data
   
   # WRONG
   - .\data:/data
   ```

2. In configuration files:
   ```json
   # CORRECT
   "path": "C:/Users/Windows/.cursor/mcp.json"
   
   # WRONG
   "path": "C:\\Users\\Windows\\.cursor\\mcp.json"
   ```

## Current Configuration
The Docker setup in [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) uses container-to-container networking with `timescaledb:5432` which is correct for Windows.
